<TEXT>
a new climate of tension pervades the middle 
east and israeli officials fear an increasingly strident war of 
words could escalate into a broader conflict 
i would say the region is entering a dangerous new phase its 
not simple rhetoric said gerald steinberg a middle east expert 
at bar ilan university near tel aviv 
israels major worry is president saddam hussein of iraq who has 
threatened to respond to any israeli attack by using weapons of mass 
destruction such as poison gas to destroy half of israel 
prime minister yitzhak shamir has countered with a warning that 
israel will defend itself if necessary 
adding to the tension is a recent palestinain raid israels long 
political crisis the likud governments refusal to participate in 
peace talks and the furor in arab countries over immigration of 
soviet jews to israel 
iraqs potential to produce biological weapons and its alleged 
desire for nuclear weapons are especially worrisome when coupled 
with its development of longrange missiles and reported plans to 
build a giant gun capable of hitting israel 
israeli officials and independent analysts said they did not 
expect iraq or other arab nations to launch a deliberate attack now 
but they said the atmosphere of tension and escalating rhetoric 
could trigger an unintended conflict 
yossi olmert director of the government press office said 
the situation is one in which talk of peace has stopped and talk 
of war has started 
iraq has already made moves that israel considers threatening 
for example israeli officials and analysts said iraq staged a 
ground forces exercise near the border with jordan moved missiles 
closer to israel in extreme western iraq and set up a joint air 
squadron with jordan that brought iraqi pilots to the israeli 
frontier 
sources who spoke on condition of they not be identified said the 
new iraqi threat added to israels defense burden requiring the 
military to go on alert when iraq moved forces in ways that could 
endanger israel 
also the prospect of a new round of palestinian terrorism has 
increased dramatically following a plo factions attempted seaborne 
raid on may 30 aimed at beachfront hotels on the jewish holiday of 
shavuot 
mohammed abbas head of the palestine liberation front which 
launched the raid told the kuwait daily alwatan that it was the 
beginning of a combat effort against the israeli enemy 
israeli security officials fear soviet jewish immigrants may 
become the next targets as they travel from moscow to israel via 
transit points in east europe such as bucharest romania and 
budapest hungary 
the foiled terror attack was a reprisal for the may 20 massacre 
of seven unarmed arab laborers by an israeli who authorities said 
was deranged 
eighteen palestinians and two israelis died in subsequent rioting 
and violence in the occupied west bank and gaza strip that gave new 
impetus to the 30monthold palestinian uprising 
shamirs rightwing government has been blamed for provoking 
tensions by encouraging new jewish settlements in occupied areas 
and rejecting us terms for a dialogue with palestinians in cairo 
foreign secretary douglas hurd of britain called on israel 
recently to engage palestinians in negotiations a tremor of 
danger may shake the region and if things drift further we risk a 
damaging escalation of violence he told reporters 
aharon levran a retired israeli brigadier general said that 
without assurance of soviet military and political support the arabs 
were unlikely to risk launching a war i dont see the arabs going 
to war now against israel when the international circumstances are 
not right levran said 
joseph alpher of the jaffee center for strategic studies in tel 
aviv said one cannot ignore the possibility that rhetoric will 
turn into an interarab commitment to genuinely escalate matters 
he said israels protracted political crisis and shamirs refusal 
to engage in peace talks weakened israels relationship with the 
united states and made israel look more vulnerable to radical arab 
states 
israel could do much to defuse tensions by starting a dialogue 
with palestinians and assuring the arabs that israel would not 
subsidize or encourage soviet jews to settle on occupied land he 
said 
its within our power to set things right alpher said 
dore gold also an analyst at the jaffee center said too much 
attention had been given to the palestinian problem while the 
overall arabisraeli arms race was ignored 
i think things can slip out of control unless a strong effort 
is made to promote declaratory confidence building measures among 
middle east nations he said 
</TEXT>
