<TEXT>
two of jerome robbins finest ballets and another 
that audiences love made up the delightful varied program on the 
second night of the new york city ballets june 5 17 festival of 
jerome robbins ballets 
dances at a gathering performed wednesday at the new york 
state theater has been highly acclaimed by critics and an audience 
favorite since the company premiered it in 1969 to about an hour of 
chopin played by pianist jerry zimmerman 10 dancers take solos 
duets trios and multiple trios 
the ballet flows from one scene to another its plotless but 
relationships can be read into it the mood of much of it is 
friendly but there are also duets of gentle rapture 
among the 10 dancers we were most struck by darci kistler who 
enlivened scenes she appeared in and jock soto who has real stage 
presence 
robbins has dedicated this ballet to the memory of dance and 
broadway lighting designer jean rosenthal 
lighting is important to robbins and lighting in dances at a 
gathering and glass pieces was superb 
the 20minute glass pieces which robbins choreographed in 
1983 to music by philip glass is a sophisticated gem one of the 
most successful modern ballets 
the back wall looks like a big piece of graph paper fortythree 
dancers move in intricate purposeful precise formations it looks 
like wall street at lunch hour 
in the second of three pieces of music maria calegari and adam 
luders dance a duet center stage with a spotlight on them a line 
of dancers across the back of the stage in dim blue light moves in 
repeated unison figures we couldnt take our eyes off that linear 
movement as it echoed the hypnotic repeated short phrases of music 
the evening began with the brief circus polka igor 
stravinsky composed the music in 1942 at george balanchines 
instigation for the ringling brothers barnum and bailey circus 
robbins choreographed it for the new york city ballets 
stravinsky festival in 1972 with 54 baby ballerinas from the school 
of american ballet he was ringmaster snapping a whip to send rows 
of little girls into place and finally into forming stravinskys 
initials 
it was a sweet curtain raiser on wednesday with jeppe mydtskov 
as ringmaster 
