sen wyche fowler dga wants to put his 
agricultural marketing reform legislation into the 1990 farm bill 
the measure would modify the agriculture departments grading 
standards of fruit and vegetables by including flavor sugar content 
and nutritional value as grading criteria 
the current system of some produce relies solely on its exterior 
appearance with no regard for the quality of the fruit or vegetable 
fowler said 
sometimes pesticides are used to enhance the looks of produce 
when external appearance is irrelevant such as in fruits or 
vegetables used by juice makers 
both consumers and farmers will benefit from this amendment 
fowler said wednesday consumers will be eating healthier food 
with less pesticides and farmers will be reducing their costs by 
spending less money on pesticides 
