rose to 639767 by march 1990 ungaro said 
the news circulation fell from 693943 in march 1989 to 526147 
in march 1990 largely because of a decision to scale back 
circulation outside the detroit area and to make the news an 
afternoon paper instead of retaining most of the previous morning 
editions ungaro said 
id have to say that the readers are voting with their 
pocketbooks every day by buying the product he said 
ungaro said the only alternative to joas is the loss of some of 
the nations oldest and best newspapers knightridder which owns 
the free press had indicated it would close the moneylosing 
newspaper if the joa were denied 
is one paper with a monopoly better than two voices in the 
community i dont think so ungaro said 
the supreme court upheld former attorney general edwin meeses 
approval of the detroit joa on a 44 vote last year 
