the spending limit initiatives 
us secretary of transportation samuel k skinner said he was 
delighted with the vote he said it validates the bush 
adminstrations argument that voters are willing to raise taxes for 
highways and other transportation needs 
californias gas tax ranks 47th in the nation well below the 
national average of 158 cents a gallon if other states taxes stay 
the same california will rank 23rd after proposition 111 goes into 
full effect in five years 
proposition 111 was extremely popular in freewaylaced cities but 
soundly rejected in the most rural regions 
