funding for a single election in california history and voters 
approved them all they provide 150 million to house the homeless 
and 2 billion to build prisons make government buildings safer and 
upgrade schools and universities 
the impetus for passage of the gasoline tax and rail bonds was 
the growing congestion on californias freeways californias 
population has been increasing about 10 times faster than the 
capacity of its highways 
as a result the average freeway speed during rush hour has 
dropped in los angeles and other urban areas to about 20 mph 
deukmejian maintained that was costing californians millions of 
dollars annually in wasted fuel and million of hours in wasted time 
