university of michigan colleagues said he was a medical maverick by 
the time he completed his residency in 1958 
hes a loner said dr murray levin an internal medicine 
specialist in bloomfield hills hes dropped out of medical 
circles as far as i know it bothers me why a guy so competent 
is retired 
hes always been a free thinker said dr gerald abrams a 
former classmate of kevorkians and now a professor of pathology at 
the university of michigan medical school he always impressed us 
as being very bright very sincere his arent exactly mainstream 
ideas 
kevorkian worked from 1959 to 1966 at pontiac general hospital 
then operated a diagnostic clinic in southfield for three years 
from 1969 to 1976 he was laboratory director at saratoga general 
hospital in detroit then worked at several small hospitals in the 
los angeles area before returning to michigan 
unable to find work within a medical community hostile to his 
views kevorkian said he retired in 1982 to study ethics write 
articles for european medical and law journals his friends recalled 
the surrealistic oil paintings he produced about 15 years ago with 
medical themes and titles like nausea fever and coma 
theyre pretty powerful kevorkian said theyre not great 
art but theyve got a lot of impact i like to shake people up 
