<TEXT>
manuel h johnson who as vice chairman of the 
federal reserve helped steer the nations monetary policy for the 
past 3 years announced his resignation today to return to academic 
life 
johnson 41 was appointed to the fed by president reagan on feb 
7 1986 and became vice chairman on aug 4 of that year he said 
his resignation would be effective aug 3 at the end of his term as 
vice chairman his term on the central bank would have ended aug 
21 2000 
there was no immediate comment from the white house on a 
successor 
as fed vice chairman johnson helped steer monetary policy 
through the last half of the nations longest peacetime economic 
expansion 
for more than a year the central bank has sought to stem 
inflation by keeping a tight grip on credit without tipping the 
economy into a recession the result continued but slow economic 
growth has become known as the soft landing 
i am extremely proud to have played a part in the unprecedented 
period of sustained economic growth and low inflation that has 
characterized the decade of the 1980s and continues into the 
1990s johnson said in his letter of resignation to president bush 
although there are still major issues to be addressed as this 
country moves ahead i feel optimistic about our future indeed 
part of my reasoning for leaving at this time is the confidence i 
have in my colleagues at the federal reserve and in the economic 
team you have assembled in your administration he continued 
johnson said he plans to return to george mason university in 
washingtons virginia suburbs and assume the koch chair in 
international economics and become director of the center for global 
market studies 
i deeply regret but understand manley johnsons decision 
fed chairman alan greenspan said in a statement the vice chairman 
and i have been an effective team ill miss him 
the fed is the nations central bank whose primary responsibility 
is monetary policy its federal open market committee actually makes 
the key decisions affecting the cost and availability of money and 
credit 
the fed is run by a sevenmember board of governors 
headquartered in washington and a nationwide network of 12 district 
banks the governors are appointed by the president and confirmed by 
the senate to serve 14year terms 
the newest member former assistant treasury secretary david 
mullins was confirmed by the senate last month bringing the board 
to full strength 
johnson 41 served as an assistant secretary and deputy 
assistant secretary of the treasury prior to his fed appointment as 
a treasury official johnson was responsible for formulating 
economic policy initiatives and developing the administrations 
economic forecast for the budget 
he also was instrumental in designing the economic recovery tax 
act of 1981 and the tax reform act of 1986 
born in troy ala johnson was a graduate of troy state 
university and received masters and doctoral degrees in economics 
from florida state university 
from 1977 to 1981 johnson taught graduate economics at george 
mason university in suburban fairfax va where he holds a full 
professorship he and his wife have two children 
