ethiopian rebels claimed thursday they had 
killed 1870 government troops in two days of fighting early this 
week near a strategic town north of the capital 
the ethiopian peoples revolutionary democratic front in a 
clandestine broadcast said 1990 soldiers were wounded in the 
battles south of dessie the heavily defended capital of wollo 
province 
the front is a combined force of the tigre peoples liberation 
front and the ethiopian peoples democratic movement a much smaller 
group 
the broadcast monitored in kenyas capital nairobi said the 
fighting took place sunday and monday about 90 miles north of addis 
ababa 
both the rebels and president mengistu haile mariams government 
claimed victories in the same area last week 
it was impossible to verify either claim because the war zone is 
generally inaccessible to journalists and other independent 
witnesses 
if the rebels claim thursday is true the insurgents would be 
only six miles south of dessie the town is at the junction of a 
major road northeast to ethiopias red sea port of assab 
dessie is also the main depot for emergency food being 
distributed to famine victims in wollo and tigre provinces 
the food is trucked from assab the only port in government hands 
since rebels captured massawa in february 
the eritreans are fighting a threedecade war for the 
independence of ethiopias northermost province of eritrea 
the tigreans have been fighting for 15 years seeking mengistus 
ouster and the establishment of a hardline marxist state they took 
control of tigre province early last year 
