crews using bulldozers dump trucks and 
frontend loaders today began clearing away the debris left by a 
tornado that devastated this farming communitys commercial strip 
and a trailer park 
twelve people were injured but warning sirens apparently averted 
more serious casualties 
lincoln county sheriffs deputies and other public safety 
employees conducted a housetohouse search today afterward they 
said they believed every resident was accounted for 
officials estimated that the twister damaged 90 percent of the 
downtown district and more than half the residences of this eastern 
colorado plains town 
one grain silo was flattened like a beer can most of the towns 
structures were twisted masses of metal and wood and several 
railroad cars were overturned 
the sirens wailed for 10 minutes before the twister struck 
wednesday night giving residents time to take shelter officials 
and survivors said 
gov roy romer who flew to the shattered town on a national 
guard helicopter early today said he would seek a federal disaster 
declaration 
the business district is 50 to 75 percent destroyed he said 
adding that damage was likely to run into the tens of millions 
the town 80 miles east of denver is known for helping 
blizzardstranded travelers forced off interstate 70 
it was without water but limited electricity and telephone 
service were reported restored by late morning officials said 
national guardsmen brought bedding food and other supplies 
