health project said she believed antigay incidents were on the 
rise in part because of aids backlash nevertheless she said many 
of the crimes go unreported in north carolina because of the states 
sodomy law 
gay people are afraid to go to local police because of 
treatment in the past there have been people that have gone to 
police stations that have been told they are breaking a felony 
statute she said 
the data for the survey came from questionnaires sent to 650 gay 
activists and organizations nationwide the task force acknowledged 
its methods were unscientific and noted that more than half the 
groups that responded in 1988 did not do so in 1989 however the 
survey is designed to give a broad look at the prevalence of 
antigay incidents 
