<TEXT>
the wife of us hostage thomas 
sutherland who marks his fifth year in captivity saturday said she 
does not bear a grudge against his shiite moslem kidnappers 
i dont feel bitter it doesnt do you any good to feel 
bitter jean sutherland said in an interview at her office on the 
campus of the american university of beirut 
mrs sutherland 56 lives and works at the campus in moslem west 
beirut continuing the work she and her husband were doing before he 
was kidnapped june 9 1985 
tom and i are just ordinary people who came here to do a job 
the job is still there and were still doing it and we just have to 
hang tough as long as we have to she said 
i was just determined that the continuity should go ahead that 
there shouldnt be changes she added this has been 
tremendously rewarding for me 
scottishborn sutherland 59 of fort collins colo is the 
second longestheld hostage in lebanon he was dean of agriculture 
at the university when he was kidnapped on the airport highway a few 
minutes after he returned from a visit to the united states 
in addition to sutherland 15 other westerners are missing in 
lebanon including five americans 
terry anderson chief middle east correspondent of the associated 
press is the longest held anderson was kidnapped in beirut on 
march 16 1985 
islamic jihad or islamic holy war the proiranian shiite group 
that holds sutherland has never issued a photo of him the only 
word on his welfare has come from former hostages who had been held 
with him 
mrs sutherland a tall woman with short dark gray hair never 
loses her smile even when she talks about the pain of her husbands 
captivity 
she is known among her colleagues as a strong determined woman 
who spends most of her time at work teaching english for beginners 
in her free time she jogs plays tennis and walks 
mrs sutherland said she has not changed anything in her house 
since her husband was abducted 
if tom walked through the door today the house would look just 
as though he left yesterday maybe thats part of what you do to 
make do and keep going in our situation i never count days or 
hours or weeks or years she said 
mrs sutherland described the house on campus and overlooking 
the mediterranean as very welcoming its something that 
refreshes the spirit 
theres so much activity on the campus green that even if im 
at home on my own i never feel alone she said 
the sutherlands have three daughters ann 32 kit 30 and joan 
26 they all live and work in the united states 
sutherland has never seen his only granddaughter simone 3 she 
was born to ann after his abduction 
mrs sutherland has a gardener one of my luxuries who 
tends the flowering trees jasmin and gardenias 
she moves freely around beirut doing her shopping and going out 
to dinner without feeling afraid 
people are really nice to me nobody has ever threatened me i 
never feel it she said 
people live under such awful conditions here and youre really 
at essence youre down to the basics what you find is that people 
come together and interact 
human relationships become the most precious thing youve got 
</TEXT>
