a former playboy model was convicted thursday of 
failing to pay taxes on almost 400000 she got from an elderly 
millionaire who allegedly paid her and her twin sister for 
companionship or sex 
the jury deliberated about 3 hours before finding leigh ann 
conley 35 guilty on four misdemeanor counts of failing to file 
federal income tax returns on about 398000 
the conviction came a month after her twin lynnette harris was 
found guilty of evading taxes on 686000 she received from the same 
suburban milwaukee businessman the late david kritzik of shorewood 
the identical blonde twins appeared nude in playboy magazine and 
in two films i the jury and sorceress before joining 
three other young women in befriending kritzik who died last summer 
at age 89 
in ms harris trial the government alleged the money she 
received from kritzik was in exchange for sex in ms conleys case 
prosecutors charged she accepted the money in exchange for her 
companionship rather than for sex 
