appealed my feeling is the hype this case received made it very 
difficult for the jury to separate the law and facts from the 
emotion starobin said 
assistant us attorney mel johnson the prosecutor in both 
cases said he was satisfied with the verdicts 
us district judge thomas curran scheduled sentencing for ms 
conley for aug 29 
ms harris who is to be sentenced july 25 could receive a 
maximum of 12 years in prison and fines totaling 625000 the 
