in closing arguments johnson described kritzik as a millionaire 
who craved the company of young women and was willing to pay for 
it he wanted a relationship with ms conley he paid for it and he 
got it 
there isnt one single witness the government brought that said 
they could show there was a service contract starobin said 
there was a good relationship a happy relationship for both of 
them he wanted her to be happy and he had the ability 
he argued the money was given as a gift and did not constitute 
income the prosecution countered that kritzik never designated the 
