<TEXT>
conagra inc has agreed to buy beatrice co 
for 134 billion in cash and stock the two food giants announced 
thursday 
the deal completes the breakup and sale of beatrice owner of 
such brand names as hunts wesson and and reddiwip by the 
investment firm kohlberg kravis roberts amp co 
kohlberg kravis bought beatrice then a major part of a huge 
foods and consumer products conglomerate in 1986 for 61 billion 
in what was then the biggest leveraged buyout ever the term 
leveraged buyout refers to purchasing a company with borrowed cash 
corporations bought in this way often are broken up and sold to 
repay the loan and make a profit 
since the buyout beatrice has sold off most of its businesses 
but still retains such wellknown food brands as hunts wesson 
manwich peter pan snack pak swiss miss la choy swift premium 
butterball eckrich and reddiwip 
conagra an omahabased diversified food company with annual 
sales of more than 15 billion sells fozen foods with such labels 
as healthy choice banquet morton and chun king as well as armour 
processed meats and country pride chicken products conagra also 
sells fertilizer animal feed and farm chemicals 
conagra last year lost a bidding war for poultry processor holly 
farms corp to tyson foods inc 
the beatrice sale will be completed after federal government 
review 
the deal calls for conagra to buy beatrice for 1150 per share 
from kohlberg kravis partnerships and management investors beatrice 
would have 12344 million shares outstanding assuming all 
outstanding warrants for purchase of beatrice shares are exercised 
the transaction would include approximately 626 million in cash 
and 710 million in conagra stock 
henry kravis a founding partner of kohlberg kravis said four 
years ago together with new management of beatrice we began the 
process of reshaping beatrice from a diverse conglomerate into a 
focused and more profitable food company todays announcement 
marks the successful completion of this process 
beatrice formerly was one of the nations biggest food and 
consumer products conglomerates owning product lines that included 
cocacola bottlers huntwesson foods swifteckrich meats stiffel 
lamps samsonite luggage tropicana juices max factor cosmetics and 
the avis car rental agency 
after the buyout beatrice began selling most of its businesses 
in order to pay off the buyout debt and generate a return for 
investors who put up money for the deal 
for example avis was sold to a group led by its employees 
tropicana to seagram co ltd beatrices international food 
businesses to the investment firm tlc international and a score of 
other companies to a group led by former beatrice chairman donald p 
kelly 
