halted more than 40 years ago in a controversy over the librarys 
award of a prize to interned american poet ezra pound 
the new rebekah johnson bobbit national prize for poetry is named 
after president lyndon b johnsons sister who met her future 
husband while working in the librarys cataloguing department in the 
1930s 
the 10000 prize will honor the best book of american poetry 
published in the preceding two years the funds will come from a 
trust created by mrs bobbitts family in her memory 
a threemember jury will select the 1990 winner in midseptember 
from nominations submitted by publishers 
the bobbitt prize will be the first poetry prize given by the 
library since it awarded the 1948 bollingen prize to pound for his 
pisan cantos afterward congress prohibited the library from 
granting awards or prizes 
