plant lost power at 1052 am local time and added during the 
course of normal functioning of the second reactor for reasons 
unapparent for the time being the shutdown system of the reactor 
became activated 
now the entire workload of electrical energy must be transfered 
to the regional electrical plant which is almost completely depleted 
of emergency fuel resources the statement said 
the statement quoted lithuanian energy minister leonas asmantas 
as saying sabotage was not suspected 
the partial fuel embargo was imposed by the kremlin to pressure 
the lithuanian parliament to suspend its march 11 declaration of 
independence 
the lithuanian information center said that as of may 28 the 
embargo had caused a 25 percent reduction in electrical power 
production in the baltic republic 
the ignalia site has two 1500megawatt reactors and it was not 
clear from the statement if both were in operation when the plant 
was shut down 
the reactors are the graphitemoderated watercooled designed 
designated rbmk in the soviet union one of which ran out of 
control and exploded at chernobyl on april 26 1986 killing 31 
