run for mayor if he steps aside and jackson does not want to do so 
however barrys spokeswoman later denied that the mayor was 
urging jackson to succeed him thats totally totally untrue 
ms rackley said 
jackson who moved to washington last year flirted with a 
candidacy before announcing in february he would not run for mayor 
mundy would not comment on the plea bargain issue during a lunch 
break from the jury selection process of the trial 
in court questioning of prospective jurors continued slowly 
us district court judge thomas penfield jackson is going 
alphabetically through a list of more than 200 people who have 
filled out questionnaires for the barry case jackson plans to 
review all 200plus applications and have lawyers for the two sides 
question them rather than stopping with a pool of 40 to 45 people as 
is more customary 
the shorter approach for picking a jury pool from which a panel 
of 12 jurors and six alternates would be chosen was used in the 
recent highprofile trials of oliver north and john poindexter 
jackson himself used such an approach in the case of former white 
house aide michael deaver 
in the barry case 37 people have been sent into the jury pool so 
far 
also on thursday the american civil liberties union said it will 
file a brief with the judge asking him to reject any plea bargain 
that includes barrys resignation 
