<TEXT>
leaders of the warsaw pact on thursday began 
transforming their 35yearold alliance from a military to a 
political body declaring the enemy image of east and west to be 
a thing of the past 
members of the kremlinled alliance also discussed various roles 
for a united germany in europe said deputy foreign minister yuli 
kvitsinsky but he indicated there was no agreement 
the leaders also declared their readiness for constructive 
cooperation with archrival nato 
they said they favor the formation of a new alleuropean 
security system and the creation of a single europe of peace and 
cooperation without artificial barriers and ideological 
hostility 
to do this it has become necessary to reconsider the character 
and functions of the warsaw treaty its members said in a 
declaration adopted at the meeting new proposals on such a 
transformation will be drawn up before the end of october 
the prevailing view was that we have to emphasize the political 
component in the warsaw treaty organization activities kvitsinsky 
said at a news conference 
soviet and east european sources familiar with the thinking of 
government leaders have said that the envisioned new political 
structure of the warsaw pact would be patterned roughly after the 
nato secretariat and council in brussels although no firm plans 
have been disclosed 
we have to broaden the consultative basis of the warsaw treaty 
organization activities and perhaps we should go in the direction 
of curtailing the military structures kvitsinsky said 
warsaw pact members include bulgaria czechoslovakia east 
germany hungary poland romania and the soviet union yugoslavia 
and albania are no longer members of the pact which has been 
criticized by some of its members as outdated given the 
prodemocratic reforms in eastern europe since 1989 
romanian president ion iliescu said the view was unanimous at the 
meeting to move away from military aspects and focus on the 
political nature of the organization founded 35 years ago 
all the participants spoke in favor of developing and adapting 
the treaty on the line of the processes under way in europe now so 
that the development of the political character of the treaty could 
be emphasized iliescu told soviet television 
czechoslovak president vaclav havel arriving in prague said the 
meeting was probably the most important in the history of this 
body because it paved the way for the warsaw pact to proceed with 
the transformation of the security order in europe 
havel said czechoslovakia presented the draft of the new order 
for the warsaw pact to its members last week and deputy foreign 
ministers from the nations worked on it through the night wednesday 
and thursday 
participants in the meeting are unanimous in their opinion that 
the ideological enemy image has been overcome by mutual efforts of 
the east and the west while the notions of east and west are again 
acquiring their purely geographical meaning the declaration said 
confrontation elements contained in documents of the warsaw 
treaty and the north atlantic treaty organization that were adopted 
in the past are no longer in line with the spirit of the times 
it said 
a provisional commission of government representatives of the 
member nations will work out proposals on transforming the alliance 
before the end of october and the political consultative committee 
the group that met in moscow on thursday will examine them 
before the end of november the declaration said 
havel said he proposed that the committees plans on a new 
security order in europe be put before a 35nation summit in paris 
in december the conference on european security and cooperation is 
the successor to the one that issued the 1975 helsinki final act 
it also called for the full implementation of the basic human 
rights and freedoms 
despite statements before the meeting by hungarian prime minister 
joszsef antall that he wants to remove his country from the 
alliance kvitsinsky said there wasnt a single statement made 
relating to a wish to quit the warsaw treaty organization 
havel too said he stressed that czechoslovakia remain in the 
pact in order to oversee its transformation 
kvitsinsky said that all participants said the warsaw pact has 
to be adapted to new circumstances 
he added that the topic of reorganizing the warsaw pacts 
integrated military command also was brought up the complex 
structure places soviet commanders over member armies in the event 
of war 
the warsaw pact members also heard a detailed report by soviet 
president mikhail s gorbachev on his washington summit last week 
with president bush 
the possibility of a united germany being a member of both 
alliances was raised kvitsinsky said along with other scenarios of 
its political and military status 
havel and czechoslovak foreign minister jiri dienstbier also 
indicated there was no agreement on future security arrangements for 
a united germany the soviets oppose nato membership for a united 
germany and gorbachev and bush failed to resolve their differences 
over the issue last week 
