already been cut 12 to 13 percent in purchasing power 
our internal planning under secretary cheneys guidance will 
bring the department of defense to a total real decline of 22 
percent by 1997 he said 
defense outlays at that point would account for their lowest 
share of federal spending since before pearl harbor even without 
the cuts congress is certain to make 
by pentagon count over the 10 years beginning in 1985 defense 
budget reductions will total 515 billion 
rice said pentagon planners began factoring a peace dividend into 
their projections five years ago 
those arguments dont take with democratic leaders and with some 
republicans in congress they think theres much more to be cut out 
