assets of 241 general purpose funds increased 101 billion to 
13030 billion assets of 102 brokerdealer funds dropped 134 
billion to 15828 billion and assets of 161 institutional funds 
fell 4753 million to 9214 billion 
short term interest rates were stable last week but buoyant 
stock and bond markets drained some assets out of money market funds 
and into longterm funds said jacob dreyer chief economist at 
the institute 
