<TEXT>
the federal government will investigate whether the 
proposed merger between norton co a us manufacturer with defense 
contracts and a french company raises national security concerns 
it was announced thursday 
executives announced the 18 billion merger between norton and 
frances compagnie de saint gobain this spring thwarting a hostile 
bid made by a british company btr plc for worcesterbased norton 
when btr was fighting for control of norton massachusetts 
politicians said they would try to block the bid because nortons 
technology should be protected 
but when saint gobain one of the worlds leading glass makers 
came forward to rescue norton with a friendly tender offer 
government officials said the deal might have to come under the same 
review 
with the news of the investigation thursday nortons stock 
dropped 150 a share to 8787 in fairly active trading on the new 
york stock exchange 
norton is a leading manufacturer of abrasives and engineering 
materials that has defense contracts with the us government the 
company with 1989 sales of 15 billion employs 16000 people and 
operates 113 plants worldwide 
